\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Installation and Usage\
\pard\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
\pard\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 To install RCEnvironment.prefPane just copy it to ~/Library/PreferencePanes or /Library/PreferencePanes and launch System Preferences.  You may have to create the directory first.\
\pard\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \
\pard\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Using RCEnvironment is very simple.  Use the '
\f5 +
\f1 ' and '
\f5 -
\f1 ' buttons to add or remove variables from the list.  Once you have set up the list of variables the way you want, just press the \'91Apply\'92 button.  Duplicate and blank names are not allowed.  At any time, you can \'91Revert\'92 back to the current state of variables.\
\pard\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \
\pard\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Once you have saved changes to your environment, you must logout and log back in for any changes to take effect.\
\pard\partightenfactor0

